entries.femaleVariant: Are we ready?
OK. The Militech convoy will be traveling from Night City to the base where they're due to meet the buyer.
V – any questions?
Seems to be a lot of abandoned stations around.
This one belonged to a corporation that ran a cement factory. They used it as their reloading point.
Didn't take the train engine when they left?
Hello, V!
Big bastard.
If you like it so much, maybe we should just hijack the train?
Yep. Then just drive this beast to the one-oh-one, there and back.
Abandoned stations – seem to be a lot around here.
Plan to move the engine how?
Plan to move this thing how, exactly?
The engine's been here going on forty years. Since the Blackwall days.
For a time, everybody had to go back to the old ways. This engine ran on nuclear. Like submarines do.
All the weirder they left it behind.
Corps. They probably listed it in a spreadsheet as "cost optimization."
It's old tech. Carol will have to hack it.
Then I'll somehow have to finagle authorization from the control tower to move it.
Let the Basilisk go on its way?
Saul would be on board with that.
We will stop it at the railroad crossing.
All we have to do is shove this beauty in its way.
Tower looks inactive to me, too.
We'll see to that. You and Panam just get the authorization code.
OK. Let's get to work.
You came after all.
[Get out]
